rComments: Professor Lopez developed a very interesting seminar in a graduate course. We studied one particular author in class, which provided us with rich discussions about multiple subjects. I developed my critical analysis skills and thought organization in the discussions with my classmates and with the professor. Be open to being mistaken and learning.
Great prof

It's easy to accidentally tune out to his lectures. We had one short assignment, a group project, and the midterm and final exam were actually easier than expected, but we did need more time and he listened to our concerns from the midterm and adjusted the final. Make sure to take notes! Prof. Lopez cares and is willing to listen and/or help.
The best prof I've had so far. He is kind, he only tests on material he puts up on his slides, and just seems like a great person.

Jose Lopez is an interesting professor with a good insight. The class is a little dry, and very theoretical, predominantly focusing on five "large" subjects. Overall, a typical sociology course, with a fair amount of readings. Lectures were a bit long, but I would take his class again.

I wish I'd taken a more interesting class with Lopez because he was kind, funny and you could tell he actually cares about his students. My class wasn't very participatory, but I think his teaching style would thrive in one that was. 1 midterm and final were combination of mc and long answer. Very straightforward. He encourages the CSL program.
Very Nice Prof! Love him!

Absolutely a spectacular guy. I found myself having issues paying attention for a few classes, but overall lectures are pretty good. His midterm was unbelievably hard if you didn't study and didn't know the readings. A really nice guy too, goes out of his way to help you succeed. His papers were pretty easy to get good marks on.
I love, love, love him!!! Wonderful prof and a great person
He's a great guy. His exams are fair, and he wants students to succeed. He went out of his way to help me understand the material -- given, you have to ask for help.
He st-st-stutters a lot, a lot. B-b-but.. he's a genuinely nice guy. And his jokes are adorable. Oh man. Love him. I just wish he wouldn't read from his powerpoints so much.
Insightful, helpful, entertaining.
he is ok in class, really funny , but it kinda gets boring when he is lecturing. i did not do any readings and i did not even take any notes, but still got a good grade.

Awesome proff..... finally at the end of my 4 years i got a proff that actually has an impact on me. Very clear on expectation and always there if you need help. Very fair marker. I serriously recommend this professor... only wish i could ahve taken more classes with him

Marx class. Very clear prof, clear expectations and tries to make it fun. Was totally surprised at how relevant Marxism is to International Development. LOVE HIM. IF YOU HAVE THE OPPORTUNITY TO TAKE ANY MORE CLASSES WITH HIM, DO IT. I would rather have been in a smaller class tho, true: bigger classes seem to overwhelm him. Cute too.
Reasonable guy, knows a lot about Marxism

After taking his course on Marx, I would have never thought again to ever take him, but he surprised me. He was funny, intelligent, clear and he just made the overall class a good experience. Take any class taught by him in 3rd or 4th year - avoid 2nd year/large classes, he gets overwhelmed easy.

Listen carefully. I do not know how this guy ended up with a PHD! He's nice, funny, and excentric which keeps things entertaining. But the man is a bit of a twit. Or maybe that's just because I took a Sociology elective :)
love him love him love him. So helpful, really interesting. Knows how to guide a discussion while still really encouraging participation. Would take another class with him any day.
my favorite prof thus far. approachable and eccentric, makes the class laugh. exams are very fair, and marking is generous. i always do well in his classes

He is a nice guy I will agree.  Lots and lots and lots...of readings.  I honestly was afraid to take another class with him.  I felt as though he was very imtimidating. But yet still seemed nice.  I was going to take Ethics..then I found out he was teaching it and I dropped it.

He's an alright teacher. Sometimes things are really unclear and sometimes it seems like he's digressing from the 'ethical' content the course is based on. The course was not what I expected at all. I'm not sure 'Soc of Ethics' is the right title for it.

Honestly, I dont know what some of these people are talking about. It was tough economic philosophy sure, but Marx is like that. The professor was good, and he repeatedly tried to help people with any questions they had, but almost no one asked any.
Good class. I feel like he is genuinely interested in the material and in teaching it.

A great professor and a very nice man.  If he is sometimes unclear in class, just tell him and he'll be more than happy to explain.  Or go to his office hours.  He is more than willing to help.  His lectures are interesting and relevant, and he's adorable.  Exams are fair, as is his marking.

He's an okay prof, interesting speaker, makes material engaging and is pretty clear. My only problem is that he looooooooves to assert his authority by humiliating students that he thinks are talking in class. I think he was picked on as a kid and is making up for it now. So, kind of a jerk.

The most ridiculous stuff that I have ever had to listen to. I think, for the midterm, he pulled the questions straight out of his (you know). There is no clarily, little consistency, and just an overall incompetence.

I cannot believe what I am reading! J-lO is the WORST professor ever! He doesn't explain ANYTHING clearly, he is a nutball and says etc.etc way too much!! If you are confused about something, he turns around and says YOU a million questions. I think that he just memorizes all of the overheads, I rea
Amazing prof.One of the best if not THE best here. I've learned so much from this class. I highly recommend it.  Bonus: hottie of the soc dept.
great teacher! always well organized lots of material in the course but overall with slides made it easier to understand. Their was alot of material but overall the course was great.
We're here to think. So, great class, excellent prof.

This class is interesting to an extent, depending on the topics. It is however a heavy workload and difficult readings, which is good because it makes us think, the class discussions are entertaining, but what is ideology, cause i still dont know!!!!

An amazing class!! Must be taken by all sociology students. Changes your thinking. Lopez is extrememly interesting. Classes fly by due to the class disscusions on cool issues. By far my favourite course in all of university. More fun than it was work.
